---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<main>
	<h3>About Me</h3>
	<p>
      I am a Cloud Security Engineer focused on securing the infrastructure behind
      AI agents, MCP servers, CI/CD pipelines, and modern cloud applications.
    </p>

    <p>
      My background combines cloud infrastructure, cybersecurity, enterprise technical
      support, DevOps, databases, networking, and systems troubleshooting. I have worked
      across environments where reliability, incident response, security, and clear
      technical communication matter.
    </p>

    <p>
      This blog is where I document the thinking behind my work: how I identify risks,
      evaluate architecture choices, harden systems, automate controls, monitor behavior,
      and learn from real technical problems.
    </p>

    <p>
      For confidentiality and security reasons, I do not publish sensitive implementation
      details from client, employer, or production environments. Instead, I focus on
      transferable lessons, safe technical patterns, architecture reasoning, and practical
      security concepts that can help others build stronger systems.
    </p>

    <h3>Current focus</h3>

    <p>
      I am especially interested in the intersection of cloud security, DevSecOps, and
      AI infrastructure security — including how to secure AI agents, MCP servers,
      cloud identities, data access, deployment pipelines, and the infrastructure that
      supports autonomous and AI-assisted systems.
    </p>

    <h3>What you will find here</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Cloud security lessons from hands-on infrastructure work</li>
      <li>DevSecOps notes around CI/CD, automation, and secure deployment</li>
      <li>Practical writeups on monitoring, logging, troubleshooting, and risk reduction</li>
      <li>Thoughts on securing AI-connected systems, MCP servers, and agent workflows</li>
      <li>Career and learning reflections as I continue growing in cloud and security</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      If you want the formal version of my experience, certifications, and technical
      background, visit my resume page.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/resume">View My Resume</a>
    </p>

</main>

